WEBVTT

00:01.347 --> 00:04.335
Did mercy and kindness
ever change your path?

00:04.360 --> 00:06.206
You could be a good lawyer if you tried.

00:06.231 --> 00:07.566
You're just not trying.

00:07.591 --> 00:09.091
LEONARD: I'm the guy who makes it worse.

00:09.127 --> 00:11.693
I'm the guy you don't
want to go up against.

00:11.729 --> 00:14.463
I... am... leaving.

00:14.498 --> 00:17.132
Seth's good. He's a good lawyer.

00:17.168 --> 00:18.500
Do you miss him?

00:18.536 --> 00:20.135
Sometimes.

00:20.171 --> 00:21.411
I won a trial. Got my client off.

00:21.446 --> 00:22.504
That's a good day.

00:22.540 --> 00:24.473
My client was a white supremacist.

00:24.508 --> 00:27.476
You won a trial because you had a trial.

00:27.511 --> 00:29.371
ROGER: It's been my dream
to have season tickets

00:29.406 --> 00:30.845
to the Yankees with you.

00:30.881 --> 00:32.213
I want to go to games with you.

00:32.247 --> 00:33.915
Thank you.

00:35.052 --> 00:37.218
♪♪

00:37.253 --> 00:40.388
♪ Ooh, yeah, yeah ♪

00:40.423 --> 00:44.225
♪♪

00:44.260 --> 00:45.393
- This is a diner.
- Yes.

00:45.428 --> 00:47.161
Why are we meeting in a diner?

00:47.197 --> 00:49.029
Because I can't get
a Denver omelet in my office.

00:49.065 --> 00:50.631
Or your office.

00:50.667 --> 00:52.500
Two years of these meetings,
we're always trapped

00:52.535 --> 00:54.402
under fluorescent lights,
sucking in recycled air,

00:54.437 --> 00:56.049
gnawing on government-issued pastries.

00:56.084 --> 00:57.499
I thought we should get out.

00:59.442 --> 01:01.075
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

01:01.110 --> 01:02.793
What's in a Denver omelet anyway?

01:02.828 --> 01:04.685
Diced ham, green peppers, onions, cheese.

01:04.720 --> 01:05.927
That's a Western omelet.

01:05.962 --> 01:07.676
Denver is in the West.

01:09.730 --> 01:11.229
What's on the agenda today?

01:11.265 --> 01:12.397
Already with the work?

01:12.433 --> 01:13.933
This is a work meeting, right?

01:13.968 --> 01:17.464
I scribbled down "complain about

01:17.499 --> 01:20.738
Draconian new sentencing
guidelines from Main Justice."

01:20.774 --> 01:24.008
"Judge Cameron."
Not sure what I meant by that.

01:24.044 --> 01:25.743
Ever been to Denver?

01:25.779 --> 01:26.911
Uh, only to the airport.

01:26.947 --> 01:29.614
They have a great bookstore
in Denver. The Tattered Cover.

01:29.649 --> 01:32.016
Anytime I fly into Denver,
I add on at least six hours

01:32.052 --> 01:33.418
for a trip to The Tattered Cover.

01:33.454 --> 01:35.053
They have great staff recommendations.

01:35.088 --> 01:36.921
I always go with a guy named "Topher."

01:36.957 --> 01:39.057
- Topher.
- I trust Topher.

01:43.429 --> 01:46.464
Uh, there was a DEA raid
on Hughes Street...

01:46.499 --> 01:48.967
you'll be getting some incoming.

01:49.002 --> 01:50.969
Uh, that's all the business I have.

01:51.004 --> 01:52.570
You gonna order? For real?

01:52.605 --> 01:54.305
You want me to order for you?

01:54.340 --> 01:57.108
That's the third DEA sweep
in that area in a month.

01:57.143 --> 01:58.976
- I wish it were more.
- You're just dragging in

01:59.011 --> 02:01.044
a bunch of low-level,
non-violent users...

02:01.080 --> 02:03.414
We're using an effective tool
against violent drug dealers

02:03.449 --> 02:05.749
who are threatening the safety
of the neighborhood.

02:05.784 --> 02:07.118
Effective? If it's so effective,

02:07.153 --> 02:08.785
why do you have to keep doing it?

02:08.821 --> 02:10.419
Denver omelet? Western omelet?

02:10.455 --> 02:12.388
There's no difference on the inside.

02:12.424 --> 02:14.390
Let's not confuse things here, either.

02:14.426 --> 02:16.793
This is a work meeting.
We should meet at work.

02:16.829 --> 02:19.129
This is a diner.

02:19.164 --> 02:21.131
This is an Archaeopteryx.

02:22.351 --> 02:23.667
Am I saying that right?

02:23.702 --> 02:26.002
I think the emphasis
is on the first syllable.

02:26.037 --> 02:28.938
- Really?
- No. I have no idea.

02:28.973 --> 02:30.072
[CHUCKLES]

02:30.108 --> 02:32.509
Lara is really into large, dead birds.

02:32.544 --> 02:35.011
- Sounds promising.
- We spent like four hours

02:35.046 --> 02:37.079
at the Natural History Museum on Sunday.

02:37.115 --> 02:40.983
Oh, this is a Phorusrhacos.

02:41.019 --> 02:43.152
"Dude, your dad is my Mobl driver."

02:43.187 --> 02:44.820
What?

02:44.856 --> 02:47.089
That is a text. You got a text.

02:47.125 --> 02:49.424
Oh. My friend Mike, what an idiot.

02:49.460 --> 02:53.029
"Yeah, not possible, and FYI,
we don't all look the same."

02:53.064 --> 02:55.297
Okay, do you want to see a Microraptor?

02:55.332 --> 02:56.966
It has...

02:57.001 --> 02:58.467
four wings.

02:58.502 --> 03:00.169
What is it?

03:01.872 --> 03:05.174
This is a picture of my dad
driving a Mobl.

03:05.209 --> 03:08.510
I'll be honest. I prefer it
to the dead bird.

03:08.546 --> 03:11.480
♪♪

03:11.515 --> 03:14.983
♪♪

03:15.018 --> 03:16.317
Favorite animal?

03:16.352 --> 03:18.119
Zebra.

03:18.155 --> 03:19.854
Favorite animal?

03:19.890 --> 03:21.189
Uh, in Australia, there are these...

03:21.224 --> 03:22.123
Favorite animal.

03:22.159 --> 03:25.526
Otter. They do that thing
with their hands.

03:25.562 --> 03:28.830
♪♪

03:28.865 --> 03:30.031
Favorite animal.

03:30.067 --> 03:31.285
Uh, Bergamasco.

03:31.320 --> 03:33.033
- Favorite animal.
- I don't have one.

03:33.069 --> 03:35.169
- If you had to choose.
- Why would I have to choose?

03:35.205 --> 03:36.873
How do you feel
when you look at this picture?

03:36.908 --> 03:38.639
Itchy. I don't like cats.

03:38.675 --> 03:39.733
It's not a cat.

03:39.768 --> 03:41.475
It looks like a cat. I don't like it.

03:41.511 --> 03:43.244
This is your new case.
Animal trafficking.

03:43.279 --> 03:45.145
This is your new case. DEA sweep...

03:45.181 --> 03:47.047
No. Please. Can we switch?

03:47.083 --> 03:48.481
No. You're the animal lady.

03:48.517 --> 03:50.684
- I'm not the animal lady.
- You're the animal lady.

03:50.720 --> 03:53.087
DEA sweep. On Hughes Street.

03:53.122 --> 03:55.689
There's been a run of drug-related
shootings in the area

03:55.725 --> 03:57.703
and that community's been
begging for more enforcement.

03:57.738 --> 03:59.226
This is more enforcement.

03:59.261 --> 04:00.493
We're on the right side of this,

04:00.529 --> 04:03.230
no matter what they're saying on
the other side of Foley Square.

04:03.265 --> 04:06.165
Reckless, swaggering, unconstitutional

04:06.201 --> 04:08.101
law-enforcement showboating.

04:08.136 --> 04:10.270
Enforcement showboating.

04:10.305 --> 04:12.739
Got it. This is the DEA sweep
on Hughes Street?

04:12.774 --> 04:14.407
Our client was literally cutting the cake

04:14.443 --> 04:16.108
at his son's birthday party
when the agents

04:16.144 --> 04:17.910
swarmed the courtyard of his building.

04:17.946 --> 04:19.178
How many others were arrested?

04:19.214 --> 04:20.613
Well, that's what's interesting.

04:20.648 --> 04:22.849
DEA 6 form says they picked up 12 people,

04:22.884 --> 04:24.450
but only 11 are in the system.

04:24.485 --> 04:26.325
Someone named "Brian Torres" is missing.

04:26.360 --> 04:27.419
- Missing?
- Missing.

04:27.455 --> 04:29.222
Torres could be a unicorn.

04:29.257 --> 04:32.258
An unimpeachable defense witness.

04:32.293 --> 04:34.293
Someone accidentally
caught up in the raid.

04:34.328 --> 04:35.161
- Mm-hmm.
- If we can find him,

04:35.196 --> 04:36.895
he might be able to help our defense.

04:36.930 --> 04:38.731
I'll call the line AUSA
and see what happened to him.

04:38.766 --> 04:41.099
No. Don't call.
Go to the DEA field office.

04:41.135 --> 04:42.934
Get out in front of this.

04:42.970 --> 04:44.936
Otter? I don't know why I said otter.

04:44.972 --> 04:47.105
And I did th-that thing with the hands.

04:47.141 --> 04:49.107
- Please don't.
- What's the case?

04:49.143 --> 04:51.877
Trafficking wildlife under
the Endangered Species Act.

04:51.912 --> 04:53.578
Red pandas... one died in transit.

04:53.613 --> 04:55.247
- That's horrible.
- I'll get through it.

04:55.282 --> 04:56.181
Next case'll be more interesting.

04:56.216 --> 05:00.585
I meant... the panda.
Dying. It's horrible.

05:00.620 --> 05:02.154
Why did Roger give you this case again?

05:02.189 --> 05:03.588
Because I don't like animals.

05:03.623 --> 05:05.323
You can see the trouble
I'm having, right?

05:05.358 --> 05:08.126
Because he knows I can approach
this logically and rationally

05:08.162 --> 05:12.497
and that I'm not gonna lose my
mind about some... furry thing.

05:12.532 --> 05:14.332
When you say "lose my mind,"

05:14.367 --> 05:16.267
do you mean feel genuine human emotion

05:16.303 --> 05:18.469
about the death of an innocent creature?

05:18.505 --> 05:19.578
Yes. You don't believe

05:19.603 --> 05:20.638
we should protect animals?

05:20.674 --> 05:23.474
For the billions of dollars we
could use to feed the hungry?

05:23.510 --> 05:24.642
Or house the homeless?

05:24.678 --> 05:27.644
To prosecute people who
commit crimes against people?

05:27.680 --> 05:29.039
- No.
- What if they're endangered?

05:29.074 --> 05:31.748
Then it's probably time for them
to go. I saw "Jurassic World."

05:31.784 --> 05:33.517
I think you need a pet.
Do you have a pet?

05:33.552 --> 05:35.186
I don't like things that lick me.

05:35.221 --> 05:36.937
First, I'll just say,
that's not a great rule.

05:36.972 --> 05:38.255
Also, you can get a fish.

05:38.291 --> 05:40.825
Point is, it's nice to have
another living creature

05:40.860 --> 05:43.026
around to talk to...
Helps you feel less lonely.

05:43.061 --> 05:45.295
Even when I was living with
Ezra, I would sometimes...

05:45.331 --> 05:46.530
I'm not lonely.

05:46.565 --> 05:49.633
Why aren't you lonely?
You should be lonely.

05:49.668 --> 05:51.201
Are you seeing someone?

05:51.236 --> 05:53.303
If you were a fish,
I'd talk to you about it.

05:53.339 --> 05:58.174
♪♪

05:58.210 --> 05:59.809
[STEAM HISSES]

06:01.546 --> 06:04.547
Dad, when did you start driving Mobl?

06:04.582 --> 06:08.218
The water in the apartment.
You notice anything?

06:08.253 --> 06:09.561
The water, what about it?

06:10.989 --> 06:12.355
Tastes fresh, huh?

06:12.390 --> 06:13.356
Why are you driving Mobl?

06:13.391 --> 06:14.824
I made an investment.

06:14.860 --> 06:18.126
After Flint, in Michigan,
everyone wants clean water.

06:18.162 --> 06:21.397
This company, Kool & Klean...
with K's... Kool, Klean...

06:21.432 --> 06:23.733
they offered a chance to distribute.

06:23.768 --> 06:26.469
Dad, please tell me you didn't
buy into some pyramid scheme.

06:26.504 --> 06:28.459
No. I buy the filters,

06:28.495 --> 06:31.139
then sell them at three times
the price I paid.

06:31.175 --> 06:32.341
And you sold...?

06:32.376 --> 06:34.476
One. To myself.

06:34.511 --> 06:37.179
Turns out this is not Flint, Michigan.

06:37.214 --> 06:40.415
New York City water is
the freshest in the country.

06:40.450 --> 06:43.252
So, now I have $5,000 worth of filters

06:43.287 --> 06:45.320
in your uncle's basement.

06:45.356 --> 06:47.923
Okay, well, $5,000 isn't a disaster.

06:47.958 --> 06:51.426
No. $5,000 isn't.

06:51.461 --> 06:53.928
Wait. Is it more than $5,000?

06:53.963 --> 06:55.830
Dad, how much are you in for?

06:55.866 --> 06:58.065
This is not your concern. It's fine.

06:58.101 --> 06:59.177
How is it fine?

06:59.212 --> 07:01.102
Coming from the guy
who can spend two hours

07:01.137 --> 07:03.271
in a grocery store
price-comparing cans of peas.

07:03.306 --> 07:06.374
I said it's fine.
I'll make the money back,

07:06.409 --> 07:08.943
you won't worry your mother with
this, and you'll go to work.

07:08.978 --> 07:11.545
This is not for you to fix.
I will fix it, okay?

07:11.580 --> 07:13.214
Okay.

07:17.120 --> 07:18.318
- The DEA raid.
- Yes.

07:18.353 --> 07:20.421
There's something wrong
with the DEA intake form.

07:20.456 --> 07:21.771
There's someone missing.

07:21.806 --> 07:23.957
What do you mean missing? Who's missing?

07:23.992 --> 07:27.394
- Brian Torres.
- Not Brian. Not Torres.

07:27.430 --> 07:29.095
Brian Torres was brought in four days ago

07:29.131 --> 07:31.064
on the Hughes Street sweep.
Is that a question?

07:31.099 --> 07:32.399
I'm representing one
of the co-defendants.

07:32.435 --> 07:33.567
I'm learning a lot.

07:33.602 --> 07:35.869
He hasn't been charged,
he wasn't processed into BOP.

07:35.905 --> 07:38.305
There are no release papers.
So I need whatever you have.

07:38.340 --> 07:42.195
I have six cookies and two more
hours until I'm done here.

07:42.911 --> 07:44.610
Here's what I have.

07:44.646 --> 07:47.580
I have the power to call you in
to testify in this case.

07:47.615 --> 07:49.882
And I can assure you, you won't like it.

07:49.918 --> 07:50.984
You look comfortable there.

07:51.019 --> 07:53.420
What I will do with you will
make you uncomfortable.

07:53.455 --> 07:55.387
So, we can do that...
I like doing that...

07:55.423 --> 07:58.123
or you can tell me
what happened to Brian Torres.

07:58.159 --> 08:00.259
[SIGHS]

08:00.294 --> 08:02.328
[KEYBOARD CLACKING]

08:02.363 --> 08:05.164
Brian Torres was checked
into Holding Room 3

08:05.199 --> 08:07.467
at 5:37 p.m. last Thursday.

08:07.502 --> 08:08.835
And released?

08:08.870 --> 08:10.470
After that.

08:10.505 --> 08:12.838
But he's obviously gone or else
we'd still have his stuff.

08:12.873 --> 08:14.106
[KEYS RATTLE]

08:15.109 --> 08:20.479
♪♪

08:20.514 --> 08:25.650
♪♪

08:25.686 --> 08:26.952
Help!

08:28.555 --> 08:30.785
I need help in here!

08:31.525 --> 08:38.381
Synced & corrected by -robtor-
www.addic7ed.com

08:40.090 --> 08:41.169
I dropped the charges.

08:41.203 --> 08:42.693
Possession, distribution, everything.

08:42.730 --> 08:44.038
You think that's even close to enough?

08:44.073 --> 08:45.774
Dropping all the charges
against your client?

08:45.809 --> 08:47.642
It should be close. You had to drop them.

08:47.678 --> 08:48.776
We didn't have to.

08:48.812 --> 08:51.645
The DEA left a witness in
a holding cell for four days.

08:51.681 --> 08:53.427
He nearly died! Do you want me

08:53.462 --> 08:55.082
to drop the charges again,
like I really mean it?

08:55.118 --> 08:57.952
I want you to bring charges
against the agent who did this.

08:57.987 --> 09:00.154
What the DEA did to Torres?

09:00.190 --> 09:03.324
Stupid, awful, tragic even.

09:03.359 --> 09:04.414
Not criminal.

09:04.450 --> 09:06.493
That's what you guys say every time.

09:06.529 --> 09:08.061
Every time it's an accident.

09:08.096 --> 09:10.564
Every time someone is shot
with their hands up,

09:10.599 --> 09:12.299
or thrown in the back of a van,

09:12.335 --> 09:14.668
or left to die in a holding cell,

09:14.704 --> 09:18.605
it's tragic and nobody is ever
responsible for the tragedy.

09:18.641 --> 09:20.073
Every time an officer...

09:20.108 --> 09:21.441
Goes on shift, he is thinking about

09:21.476 --> 09:22.575
how to violate our civil rights.

09:22.610 --> 09:23.643
He's angry. He's racist.

09:23.678 --> 09:27.113
He's calculating and deliberate
and premeditated.

09:27.149 --> 09:29.950
He's part of a goon squad
trying to inflict maximum pain

09:29.985 --> 09:32.319
on people and communities he despises.

09:32.354 --> 09:33.653
Every time.

09:33.688 --> 09:35.255
Have you watched the video?

09:35.290 --> 09:36.689
I don't need to watch the video.

09:36.725 --> 09:38.324
Try the part where he hallucinates,

09:38.360 --> 09:41.994
tries to eat his own glasses,
claws and scratches...

09:42.029 --> 09:43.062
The agent who left him there...

09:43.097 --> 09:45.030
- Fired.
- You say that like it means something.

09:45.066 --> 09:46.399
It means he's fired.

09:47.802 --> 09:49.702
I'm sorry about what happened to Torres.

09:49.738 --> 09:51.003
I am.

09:51.533 --> 09:53.138
But there's nothing to prosecute here.

09:53.174 --> 09:54.439
This was an accident.

09:57.245 --> 09:58.810
Next time you're in Denver,

09:58.846 --> 10:01.981
why don't you skip the bookstore
and drive out to Florence.

10:02.016 --> 10:04.183
ADX. Supermax.

10:04.218 --> 10:07.052
Where everyone is held in solitary.

10:07.088 --> 10:09.388
See what it does to a person.

10:09.423 --> 10:11.656
Or just watch the video on your desk.

10:11.692 --> 10:14.826
Sorry? You'll be sorry
you didn't do more.

10:14.862 --> 10:18.129
♪♪

10:18.164 --> 10:20.532
Seth Oliver's a reasonable guy, right?

10:20.567 --> 10:22.066
Career choice notwithstanding.

10:22.102 --> 10:23.535
And the fact that he broke up with you.

10:23.570 --> 10:24.903
It was mutual.

10:24.938 --> 10:26.170
- Was it?
- Yes.

10:26.206 --> 10:27.638
Huh.

10:27.673 --> 10:30.041
Why are you asking?
Do you have a case against him?

10:30.076 --> 10:33.211
No. I want to talk to him
about bringing a case,

10:33.246 --> 10:34.913
and he's the only prosecutor I know.

10:34.948 --> 10:36.180
I mean, I know Kate Littlejohn,

10:36.216 --> 10:37.815
but I'd rather get food poisoning

10:37.850 --> 10:39.217
than talk to Kate Littlejohn.

10:39.252 --> 10:41.920
Like actual food poisoning.
Like salmonella.

10:41.955 --> 10:43.587
I think I generally understand the point.

10:43.623 --> 10:45.322
Do you think Seth would talk to me?

10:45.837 --> 10:47.558
I-I think so.

10:47.593 --> 10:48.926
And he's reasonable.

10:48.961 --> 10:51.328
For the most part.
I can call him if you want.

10:51.363 --> 10:52.930
I don't want to make it awkward for you.

10:52.965 --> 10:54.064
I don't think it would be awkward.

10:54.099 --> 10:55.599
I haven't seen him in a while.

10:55.635 --> 10:57.234
It's cool. I can do it. Thanks.

10:57.269 --> 10:59.537
♪♪

10:59.572 --> 11:02.772
Your client trafficked
in endangered animals...

11:02.808 --> 11:05.075
Usually, we just pay five grand
and call it a day.

11:05.110 --> 11:06.944
And usually, I'm not involved
in these cases,

11:06.979 --> 11:09.046
so we might be doing it differently.

11:09.081 --> 11:11.214
The red panda died in transit.

11:11.250 --> 11:13.116
It was alive when it hit American soil.

11:13.152 --> 11:14.617
My client didn't kill it, Customs did.

11:14.653 --> 11:16.386
I'll be in touch after
I've checked out the body.

11:16.422 --> 11:17.587
The body?

11:17.622 --> 11:20.289
It's a panda, not a lady jogger
found by the East River.

11:20.325 --> 11:24.093
Red panda. I like to be accurate.

11:24.128 --> 11:25.895
We should grab drinks.

11:25.931 --> 11:27.229
If you're gonna be the animal lady,

11:27.265 --> 11:28.431
we're gonna be seeing each other a lot.

11:28.467 --> 11:30.099
I am not the animal lady.

11:31.336 --> 11:33.302
The holding cell tape of Brian Torres.

11:33.338 --> 11:34.403
Someone leaked it.

11:34.439 --> 11:36.305
[SIGHS] Not someone. Jill.

11:36.341 --> 11:39.308
It's all over the news. And it's awful.

11:39.344 --> 11:41.110
Draw up charges against Agent Keener.

11:41.145 --> 11:42.488
What?

11:42.523 --> 11:44.746
Draw up charges against Agent Keener.

11:44.782 --> 11:47.283
She's put us in a box here.
We need to do something.

11:47.318 --> 11:49.251
Measured, reasonable charges
that show the public

11:49.287 --> 11:50.652
that we take this seriously,

11:50.688 --> 11:53.622
but that don't piss off
our friends at the DEA...

11:53.657 --> 11:55.190
who we need.

11:56.927 --> 11:58.259
You wanted to see me?

11:58.295 --> 12:01.329
No, I wanted to drink with you.

12:01.365 --> 12:02.510
Oh.

12:02.546 --> 12:05.333
In 2004, we were up three games to none

12:05.369 --> 12:07.002
on the Red Sox in the ALCS.

12:07.037 --> 12:09.770
We, the Yankees.

12:09.806 --> 12:13.641
No team has ever come back
from three games down.

12:13.676 --> 12:17.345
So this champagne was chilled.
Ready to be drunk.

12:17.381 --> 12:19.247
This very bottle. And then...

12:19.282 --> 12:21.516
Then Mariano Rivera walks Kevin Millar

12:21.551 --> 12:23.150
in the bottom of the ninth.

12:23.185 --> 12:24.351
Mariano Rivera.

12:24.387 --> 12:27.822
Red Sox score. Win the game.
The series. The World Series.

12:27.857 --> 12:30.257
Breaking a curse going back 86 years.

12:30.292 --> 12:32.914
The only thing more incredible

12:32.950 --> 12:35.129
than what the Red Sox did that year

12:35.164 --> 12:37.798
is what Roger Gunn did today.

12:37.834 --> 12:39.500
What we made him do. Mm-hmm.

12:39.535 --> 12:42.269
The U.S. Attorney's office
actually filed charges

12:42.304 --> 12:43.837
against a federal agent.

12:43.872 --> 12:45.372
They never do this.

12:45.408 --> 12:48.042
That man, there? That's Kirk Keener,

12:48.077 --> 12:52.179
the DEA Agent who left
Brian Torres in a cell to rot.

12:52.214 --> 12:54.181
It's time to finally drink this.

12:54.216 --> 12:55.349
Mm-hmm.

12:55.384 --> 12:56.650
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

12:58.000 --> 13:04.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

13:07.195 --> 13:09.328
WOOD: Counselors,
please state your appearances.

13:09.364 --> 13:12.565
Roger Gunn and Leonard Knox for
the United States, your honor.

13:12.600 --> 13:14.833
Jill Carlan and Sandra Bell
for the defendant,

13:14.869 --> 13:18.237
DEA Special Agent Kirk Keener.

13:18.273 --> 13:24.310
♪♪

13:24.345 --> 13:26.879
Well. I'm still a judge.

13:26.914 --> 13:28.548
Let's get started.

13:33.390 --> 13:35.709
Under the condition
that Mr. Keener surrenders

13:35.734 --> 13:37.934
any and all weapons
and does not associate

13:37.969 --> 13:39.903
with the victim or the victim's family,

13:39.938 --> 13:42.371
bail is set at $250,000.

13:42.407 --> 13:44.273
Your honor, Mr. Keener
doesn't have the resources

13:44.309 --> 13:46.409
to post a quarter
of a million dollar bond.

13:46.445 --> 13:47.876
That's why I'm representing him.

13:47.912 --> 13:48.978
ROGER: It's a drop in the bucket

13:49.013 --> 13:51.147
for the Association of Federal
Drug Enforcement Agents.

13:51.182 --> 13:53.615
The union isn't giving
Mr. Keener financial assistance.

13:53.651 --> 13:55.667
He was fired. Mr. Gunn knows that.

13:55.710 --> 13:58.220
I'm going to hold at $250,000.

14:02.427 --> 14:04.259
Careful what you wish for.

14:07.264 --> 14:10.398
You're being charged with 18 USC 242,

14:10.434 --> 14:13.001
deprivation of rights under color of law.

14:13.036 --> 14:16.004
A key issue's going to be intent...

14:16.039 --> 14:18.508
[SIGHS]
whether you "willfully subjected"...

14:19.376 --> 14:20.741
You may want to listen to this.

14:20.777 --> 14:22.910
I have testified
against clients of yours,

14:22.946 --> 14:23.979
what, seven, eight times?

14:24.014 --> 14:27.015
I know what you think of
the DEA. The work we do. Me.

14:27.050 --> 14:30.952
It was five times,
and I think you're my client.

14:30.988 --> 14:32.820
I'm here to represent you.

14:34.291 --> 14:35.991
It was an accident.

14:36.026 --> 14:37.758
I arrested Torres...

14:37.794 --> 14:39.460
Even though he was clean.

14:39.496 --> 14:41.829
His name matched a suspect
in another case.

14:41.865 --> 14:45.199
I told Bill Howfield,
"Hold him while I check it out."

14:45.234 --> 14:48.503
According to the indictment,
you actually told Agent Howfield

14:48.538 --> 14:51.105
to "Leave that son of a bitch in there."

14:51.140 --> 14:53.540
[SCOFFS] Torres was screaming at me.

14:53.575 --> 14:55.542
- He was innocent.
- Well, I didn't know that.

14:55.577 --> 14:57.445
I was trying to assess the situation.

14:57.480 --> 14:58.512
I was frustrated.

14:58.547 --> 15:00.647
I told Howfield to hold him
and I'd be back.

15:00.682 --> 15:04.518
And then I got pulled onto
another bust and I... forgot.

15:04.553 --> 15:06.120
Why am I being singled out?

15:06.155 --> 15:08.288
What about everybody else
that works down there?

15:08.324 --> 15:09.966
No one else knew Torres was in that room

15:10.001 --> 15:12.458
after Howfield went off shift
and you didn't come back.

15:12.494 --> 15:13.727
You were the arresting officer.

15:13.762 --> 15:15.361
You were the one who ordered him held.

15:15.397 --> 15:17.330
It wasn't an order.

15:17.365 --> 15:21.167
I was planning on coming back.
I made a mistake.

15:21.202 --> 15:24.137
This is a problem for you, isn't it?

15:24.172 --> 15:25.805
Defending me?

15:27.618 --> 15:29.842
Everything is backwards
and weird. I don't like it.

15:29.877 --> 15:31.577
The sandwich is pretty good.

15:31.612 --> 15:33.379
Jill is defending a DEA agent

15:33.415 --> 15:36.516
because Roger is prosecuting a DEA agent.

15:36.551 --> 15:38.418
And I'm helping her. Right now?

15:38.453 --> 15:40.920
I'm supposed to be finding
character evidence

15:40.955 --> 15:42.155
for a DEA agent.

15:42.190 --> 15:43.288
It's like a weird dream

15:43.323 --> 15:45.591
where everybody's on opposite
sides and... Seth's here.

15:45.626 --> 15:47.059
Seth is in your weird dream?

15:47.094 --> 15:48.561
No. He's here. In our office.

15:48.596 --> 15:49.929
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

15:49.964 --> 15:51.396
Hey.

15:51.432 --> 15:52.531
- Hi.
- Hi.

15:52.567 --> 15:55.120
- Uh, do you know where...?
- Hey.

15:55.156 --> 15:56.943
Never mind. Found him.

15:56.979 --> 15:59.137
- You wanna go?
- Yeah.

16:03.110 --> 16:05.743
See? Weird.

16:05.779 --> 16:08.380
♪♪

16:08.415 --> 16:10.415
Thanks for coming by.
I would've come to you.

16:10.451 --> 16:12.384
I've always been curious
about this place.

16:12.419 --> 16:14.519
Ah. Never been here?
Allison never brought you here?

16:14.555 --> 16:17.121
We made a point of keeping
work and home separate.

16:17.156 --> 16:19.457
And we were actually
pretty good about that.

16:19.492 --> 16:22.860
For a few hours. Then we broke up.

16:22.896 --> 16:24.361
[SIGHS]

16:24.397 --> 16:26.064
So... whaddya need?

16:26.099 --> 16:28.499
I have a case for you.

16:30.570 --> 16:33.059
Kool & Klean. With two K's.

16:33.094 --> 16:35.872
Two K's? Like the Kool and
the Klean each starts with a K?

16:35.908 --> 16:38.476
Yes. They sell water filters,
but their parent company

16:38.511 --> 16:41.612
runs dozens of other Multi-Level
Marketing "opportunities."

16:41.647 --> 16:44.915
Nutritional supplements,
phone plans, skin care...

16:44.950 --> 16:46.049
Croissants?

16:47.286 --> 16:48.486
The donut place near my apartment

16:48.521 --> 16:50.286
sells all those things, plus croissants.

16:51.423 --> 16:52.667
I think these are scams

16:52.702 --> 16:54.491
that bilk people
out of their life's savings.

16:54.526 --> 16:57.389
Um, I thought a prosecutor
should take a look.

16:57.425 --> 16:59.014
How'd this get on your radar?

16:59.049 --> 17:01.064
My dad was one of the ones scammed.

17:01.100 --> 17:04.134
I'm not sure for how much.
A lot, I think.

17:04.169 --> 17:05.868
But yeah... my dad.

17:05.905 --> 17:07.604
That sucks. I'm sorry.

17:07.638 --> 17:08.971
I'll take a look.

17:09.007 --> 17:11.106
Thank you. I can't promise,

17:11.141 --> 17:13.182
but there might be a water
filter in it for you.

17:14.378 --> 17:17.946
[CREATURES MAKING NOISE]

17:17.982 --> 17:19.648
Oh.

17:19.684 --> 17:21.684
This little guy came in
about a month ago.

17:21.719 --> 17:23.452
He's kind of like our house dragon.

17:23.487 --> 17:25.755
If I didn't already have
a couple at home, I'd adopt him.

17:25.790 --> 17:27.957
- You want to feed him?
- Uh, no. The red panda.

17:27.992 --> 17:30.826
Can you tell me if it was dead
when it arrived in the country?

17:30.862 --> 17:33.028
Oh, yeah. Monte was dead.

17:33.053 --> 17:34.919
At least a day before he ever got here.

17:34.955 --> 17:36.588
Uh, Monte?

17:36.623 --> 17:38.856
I name them.

17:38.892 --> 17:41.392
These collectors, they act like animals

17:41.427 --> 17:42.927
are vintage salt and pepper shakers

17:42.963 --> 17:44.428
they got at a flea market.

17:44.464 --> 17:46.631
And the smugglers make bank.

17:46.666 --> 17:49.433
$23 billion last year.

17:49.469 --> 17:51.102
Their creativity would be impressive

17:51.137 --> 17:52.637
if it weren't so horrible...

17:52.672 --> 17:53.771
hidden storage in cars,

17:53.807 --> 17:57.074
stuffing birds into toilet
paper rolls in suitcases.

17:57.110 --> 17:59.276
And the fines mean nothing to them.

17:59.312 --> 18:02.113
"5OK? Sure, let me
just roll off my money pile

18:02.148 --> 18:04.881
and pick up some spare change.
Here you go."

18:04.917 --> 18:06.049
Meanwhile, they're cutting

18:06.085 --> 18:08.152
the faces off rhinos to take their horns.

18:08.187 --> 18:09.286
Do you have documentation

18:09.322 --> 18:11.322
showing the red panda arrived dead?

18:11.357 --> 18:13.256
I take photos of everyone who comes in.

18:13.291 --> 18:15.391
No one ever wants to prosecute,
but a guy can hope.

18:15.427 --> 18:17.094
I still have the body.
Do you want to see?

18:17.129 --> 18:18.261
Yes.

18:18.296 --> 18:20.163
Here. Hold Mango.

18:20.198 --> 18:21.397
Ohh.

18:25.203 --> 18:27.070
Follow me.

18:27.106 --> 18:29.672
These ones over here are all
gonna go to zoos or sanctuaries.

18:29.707 --> 18:31.674
We can usually find homes
for the cute or the rare.

18:31.709 --> 18:34.644
But 20 baby eels, or a turtle
or a guy like Mango there?

18:34.679 --> 18:36.179
Probably not.

18:36.214 --> 18:38.181
People want snuggly and furry and cute...

18:38.216 --> 18:40.783
something they can pet.
Mango's just... Mango.

18:40.818 --> 18:42.018
Not trying to impress.

18:42.053 --> 18:43.153
What happens to those?

18:43.188 --> 18:45.688
Depends on your religion, I guess.

18:45.723 --> 18:48.924
Main reason I took this job
is I love animals.

18:48.960 --> 18:50.860
Same reason you have the case, right?

18:50.895 --> 18:53.162
Uh, little different.

18:53.197 --> 18:55.164
Now I mostly just put them to sleep.

18:55.199 --> 18:56.666
The body's in there.

19:02.906 --> 19:04.640
You're going after this guy, right?

19:04.675 --> 19:07.509
I know it's a lot of work
for just a small fine.

19:07.545 --> 19:10.045
But Monte would appreciate it, I think.

19:10.080 --> 19:11.813
Thank you for your time.

19:11.848 --> 19:14.483
Can you take... uh, Mango?

19:14.518 --> 19:16.318
- Yeah.
- Thanks.

19:16.353 --> 19:18.019
Ooh.

19:27.230 --> 19:29.030
How'd it go with Keener?

19:29.066 --> 19:31.166
He doesn't trust me.

19:31.201 --> 19:33.902
I'm sure it'll take a little time.

19:33.937 --> 19:36.075
On both sides.

19:36.872 --> 19:38.539
Do you watch law shows on TV?

19:38.575 --> 19:39.674
No.

19:39.709 --> 19:41.075
You're not missing a whole lot.

19:41.110 --> 19:43.544
They always have
defense lawyers struggling

19:43.580 --> 19:46.046
with how they can
defend their horrible clients.

19:46.082 --> 19:48.416
Do you know how often
I ever feel that struggle?

19:48.451 --> 19:50.551
- Never.
- Not ever.

19:50.587 --> 19:53.220
It's a total fiction about who we are

19:53.255 --> 19:55.723
and the work we do and the way
we approach this job.

19:55.758 --> 19:58.225
But this one is difficult.

19:58.260 --> 20:01.095
I've spent my whole career going
up against people like Keener.

20:01.130 --> 20:03.063
Then this isn't gonna help.

20:03.099 --> 20:04.732
Four formal complaints against Keener

20:04.767 --> 20:06.834
when he served in the
Jacksonville Vice Unit.

20:06.869 --> 20:09.035
Mistreatment of a suspect,
two wrongful arrests,

20:09.070 --> 20:11.170
plus denying a prisoner his medication.

20:13.041 --> 20:15.275
If they call to make a deal,
take the call.

20:15.310 --> 20:16.809
Get whatever you can.

20:27.255 --> 20:30.623
Seven colleagues, partners,
witnesses at the DEA

20:30.658 --> 20:32.191
who could testify against Keener.

20:32.227 --> 20:34.093
All gone. Unavailable. Unreachable.

20:34.129 --> 20:36.295
Plus they're dragging
their feet on discovery.

20:36.330 --> 20:38.631
Other than this one agent, Bill Howfield,

20:38.666 --> 20:40.966
we don't have anything.
DEA's freezing us out.

20:41.001 --> 20:42.934
I don't understand, they fired the guy.

20:42.970 --> 20:44.270
They had to cut him loose.

20:44.305 --> 20:45.771
Doesn't mean
they had to turn against him.

20:45.806 --> 20:47.072
They'll protect him.

20:47.107 --> 20:49.475
Build a wall around
a terminated colleague.

20:49.510 --> 20:50.876
We're at that wall.

20:50.911 --> 20:52.278
And it's only gonna get higher.

20:52.313 --> 20:53.412
And it won't just be this case.

20:53.447 --> 20:54.480
It'll be everything we do.

20:54.515 --> 20:57.315
The agencies will start
routing things to Brooklyn.

20:57.350 --> 20:59.751
Locals. We will pay for this.

20:59.787 --> 21:03.188
The office. Me. You.

21:05.159 --> 21:07.125
Make the call.

21:13.047 --> 21:15.642
You. Me. This room. Never gets old.

21:15.667 --> 21:18.268
Good. Then you won't mind
that I'm not leaving here

21:18.303 --> 21:20.069
until you reduce the charges
to a misdemeanor.

21:20.105 --> 21:21.010
Never gonna happen.

21:21.045 --> 21:22.638
I can set up a cot in that corner.

21:22.673 --> 21:24.540
- You will be here forever.
- I live out of a bag.

21:24.575 --> 21:26.242
This will not be difficult for me.

21:26.277 --> 21:28.377
- I want to tell you something.
- Oh, God.

21:28.412 --> 21:29.378
Not some fake sob story

21:29.413 --> 21:32.115
about your boyhood dreams
of being Superman.

21:32.150 --> 21:33.216
No, this is a true story,

21:33.251 --> 21:35.451
and it belongs to an innocent
man named Brian Torres.

21:35.486 --> 21:38.254
I know you're feeling very
righteous after Jared Nash.

21:38.289 --> 21:39.743
I get it. I do. But if we're gonna talk

21:39.779 --> 21:42.558
about an innocent man,
let's talk about Kirk Keener.

21:42.593 --> 21:45.494
A distinguished federal agent
who made a mistake.

21:45.529 --> 21:47.162
This is...

21:47.197 --> 21:48.196
Unbelievable?

21:48.232 --> 21:49.767
I literally want to be saying
what you're saying.

21:49.802 --> 21:51.919
Then we should be able
to figure this out.

21:55.005 --> 21:57.572
Is this your animal case?
I thought you were settling that.

21:57.607 --> 22:00.608
The only way this stops
is if I push for jail time.

22:00.644 --> 22:02.610
The smugglers are making millions.

22:02.646 --> 22:05.480
The fines are no more
than a tax. Not settling.

22:05.515 --> 22:06.481
What is that?

22:06.516 --> 22:08.150
Kool & Klean. Two K's.

22:08.185 --> 22:10.018
Two K's? That's not good.

22:10.053 --> 22:12.186
I'm looking into a case for Jay Simmons.

22:12.221 --> 22:14.021
- Ohh. Also not good.
- I like Jay.

22:14.056 --> 22:16.391
He's different than he was
when you went up against him.

22:16.426 --> 22:17.458
Oh, I doubt that.

22:17.494 --> 22:18.733
People change. You weren't into animals.

22:18.768 --> 22:20.461
And now you're like the anima...
I am not.

22:20.497 --> 22:22.997
I'm just trying to understand
the other side.

22:23.032 --> 22:25.933
I'm just trying to do my job.
That is all this is.

22:25.968 --> 22:27.296
I like animals, too.

22:27.321 --> 22:29.287
Allison and I were gonna get a dog,

22:29.312 --> 22:31.379
but then it didn't seem like
she really wanted a dog.

22:31.404 --> 22:32.537
Or me.

22:32.741 --> 22:36.043
I saw her over there. In the office.

22:36.078 --> 22:38.813
It's weird when you talk
to someone every single day

22:38.848 --> 22:41.348
and then suddenly you don't
talk to them at all.

22:41.383 --> 22:43.650
Maybe that could be us someday.

22:44.853 --> 22:47.220
Keener admits to a civil violation.

22:47.255 --> 22:50.524
Pays a $10,000 fine, and they
drop the criminal charge.

22:50.559 --> 22:52.726
No trial, no jail time.

22:52.761 --> 22:55.429
That's good. I'll take it to Keener.

22:56.765 --> 22:57.864
I worked it out with Sandra Bell.

22:57.899 --> 22:59.333
Keener admits to a civil violation,

22:59.368 --> 23:00.634
we drop the criminal charge.

23:00.669 --> 23:01.968
No need to worry about that DEA wall.

23:02.003 --> 23:04.304
Draft the agreement.

23:04.339 --> 23:06.739
♪♪

23:06.774 --> 23:08.541
You pay a $10,000 fine...

23:08.576 --> 23:10.676
And say that I violated his rights,

23:10.712 --> 23:12.745
like this was police brutality.

23:12.780 --> 23:15.198
And never work in law enforcement again.

23:15.233 --> 23:18.217
And avoid years in prison.

23:18.252 --> 23:21.787
Which is what you're facing
if we try this and lose.

23:23.391 --> 23:24.990
Look, it's your choice.

23:25.025 --> 23:26.892
I just want you to understand the risks.

23:26.927 --> 23:29.762
The risks? You're telling me about risk?

23:29.797 --> 23:34.432
Do you have any idea what I do?
The choices that I've made?

23:34.468 --> 23:36.902
The risks that I take every day?

23:36.937 --> 23:39.838
I risk my life for other people

23:39.874 --> 23:43.675
because I genuinely believe in what I do.

23:43.710 --> 23:45.625
And I know that you look at me
and you think

23:45.661 --> 23:48.676
that I'm just part of the system
that has abused your clients.

23:48.677 --> 23:50.810
Well, I am not the system.

23:50.845 --> 23:53.513
I am a man who works hard.

23:53.548 --> 23:55.348
Who has tried my best.

23:55.383 --> 23:59.519
And, yes, I am flawed. I make mistakes.

23:59.554 --> 24:01.521
I-I-I have gotten emotional.

24:01.556 --> 24:02.989
I've over-reacted.

24:03.024 --> 24:05.158
I'm a human being and I make mistakes,

24:05.193 --> 24:07.126
and I made a mistake here.

24:08.722 --> 24:10.896
But it was a mistake.

24:13.835 --> 24:15.735
This is the deal.

24:17.571 --> 24:19.672
You tell me what you want me to do.

24:20.742 --> 24:21.907
[STAMMERS]

24:21.943 --> 24:25.043
If you think that I should take
the deal, then I'll take it.

24:25.447 --> 24:27.379
I've seen you.

24:27.866 --> 24:30.549
I know what you can do.
I know how good you are.

24:30.584 --> 24:32.651
I just want you to fight as hard for me

24:32.686 --> 24:34.653
as you do for everybody else.

24:37.924 --> 24:40.191
That is what I will do.

24:40.226 --> 24:45.396
♪♪

24:45.431 --> 24:50.568
♪♪

24:50.603 --> 24:55.540
♪♪

24:55.575 --> 25:00.844
♪♪

25:00.880 --> 25:06.050
♪♪

25:06.085 --> 25:11.189
♪♪

25:11.224 --> 25:17.061
♪♪

25:17.096 --> 25:20.497
<i>Hey! Hello?!</i>

25:20.532 --> 25:22.733
<i>Let me... Let me talk to my family.</i>

25:22.768 --> 25:25.502
<i>Come on!</i>

25:25.537 --> 25:28.238
<i>Oh, man! Come on!</i>

25:28.273 --> 25:31.575
<i>Let me call my family! This is not right!</i>

25:31.610 --> 25:36.279
<i>Let me out!!</i>

25:36.315 --> 25:38.348
[ <i> GROANING, CRYING</i> ]

25:43.722 --> 25:46.055
I need help.

25:48.760 --> 25:51.728
[POUNDING ON DOOR]

26:00.605 --> 26:03.039
I watched it.

26:03.074 --> 26:05.942
What the DEA did to Torres?

26:05.977 --> 26:09.978
Stupid, awful, tragic even. Not criminal.

26:12.317 --> 26:14.016
[SCOFFS] Really, Jill?

26:14.051 --> 26:16.185
You're the one who wanted me
to press charges.

26:17.254 --> 26:19.087
Just like that. On the other side.

26:19.123 --> 26:20.656
Just like you.

26:21.826 --> 26:23.292
What side do you think I'm on?

26:23.328 --> 26:25.294
Torres is a victim. I represent victims.

26:25.329 --> 26:27.562
You represent the government.

26:27.597 --> 26:30.098
On behalf of the victims.

26:30.134 --> 26:33.535
The victims are the people
being abused by the government.

26:33.570 --> 26:35.691
You don't believe that.
Is that what you really believe?

26:35.726 --> 26:37.121
That's what I've always believed.

26:37.157 --> 26:40.209
Keener is as much
a victim here as Torres.

26:40.244 --> 26:42.210
You're on the wrong side of this.

26:42.245 --> 26:44.212
I'm on the opposite side of you.

26:44.247 --> 26:46.280
I think that's where I want to be.

26:48.484 --> 26:50.217
We're withdrawing the plea offer.

26:50.252 --> 26:52.118
I'll see you at trial.

26:53.356 --> 26:55.756
Agent Howfield, you were on duty
the night Agent Keener

26:55.791 --> 26:58.492
booked Brian Torres into Holding
Room number 3, is that right?

26:58.527 --> 27:00.561
- That's right.
- Did Agent Keener say anything

27:00.596 --> 27:01.829
to you about Mr. Torres at that time?

27:01.864 --> 27:05.398
He said, "Leave that son of a
bitch in there. I'll be back."

27:05.433 --> 27:07.133
Did Mr. Keener ever come back?

27:07.169 --> 27:08.301
No, sir. He did not.

27:08.337 --> 27:12.405
You ever hear a DEA agent or
other law enforcement official

27:12.440 --> 27:15.141
refer to a suspect as a "son of a bitch"?

27:15.177 --> 27:16.509
Yes.

27:16.544 --> 27:18.178
Worse?

27:18.213 --> 27:20.246
All the time. Every day.

27:20.281 --> 27:24.250
Did you tell anyone that
Mr. Torres was in that room

27:24.285 --> 27:26.686
when you went off shift, Agent Howfield?

27:26.721 --> 27:28.254
No.

27:28.714 --> 27:30.356
Why not?

27:31.758 --> 27:33.359
Forgot.

27:33.395 --> 27:37.329
♪♪

27:37.365 --> 27:40.099
Ms. Blake, you maintain
the video surveillance system

27:40.134 --> 27:42.201
at the DEA Field Office
in Manhattan, correct?

27:42.236 --> 27:43.269
I do.

27:43.304 --> 27:44.703
Have you had an opportunity

27:44.738 --> 27:46.785
to review the surveillance video
of Holding Room 3?

27:46.821 --> 27:47.847
Objection!

27:47.882 --> 27:49.985
Let's take a brief recess.

27:52.679 --> 27:54.379
The only purpose of that video

27:54.415 --> 27:55.947
is to inflame the jury.

27:55.982 --> 27:56.882
The purpose of the video

27:56.917 --> 27:57.883
is to establish an element
of the offense.

27:57.918 --> 27:59.687
You want to put on the video
because you know

27:59.722 --> 28:02.344
that it is so horrifying that
no jury can watch it and...

28:02.379 --> 28:04.459
I want to put on the video
because it's my right

28:04.494 --> 28:05.633
to put on my case the way I see...

28:05.669 --> 28:08.328
We'll agree to a few stills
from the video, Your Honor.

28:08.329 --> 28:10.528
Stills is gonna break down
the video so it's worthless.

28:10.564 --> 28:12.163
That's what you do every time you decide

28:12.199 --> 28:13.699
not to try an officer, isn't it?

28:13.734 --> 28:15.300
How many times have we seen your boss

28:15.335 --> 28:17.235
stand in front of a bank
of cameras telling us

28:17.270 --> 28:19.370
that we're not seeing what we
think we're seeing?

28:19.406 --> 28:21.306
"The video doesn't tell the whole story."

28:21.341 --> 28:22.975
Well, in this case, it doesn't.

28:23.010 --> 28:24.142
In this case, we did charge an officer.

28:24.177 --> 28:25.310
How big of you.

28:25.345 --> 28:26.877
Ms. Carlan. Mr. Gunn.

28:27.481 --> 28:29.380
I'm enjoying it. I-I really am.

28:29.416 --> 28:31.916
I wish you could switch sides
every week or so.

28:32.653 --> 28:35.686
I think our system might be
better for the perspective.

28:35.722 --> 28:38.323
But we need to move forward now.

28:42.795 --> 28:45.329
TORRES: <i>Can I call my family?</i>

28:45.364 --> 28:48.766
<i>Hey! We got to call my family!</i>

28:48.801 --> 28:51.836
<i>We got to call my family!</i>

28:51.871 --> 28:54.905
[ <i> POUNDING</i> ]

28:54.941 --> 28:57.574
<i>Oh, man! Come on!</i>

28:57.610 --> 29:00.010
<i>Let me call my family! This is not right!</i>

29:00.045 --> 29:01.845
<i>Hello?!</i>

29:01.880 --> 29:03.213
[ <i> POUNDS ON DOOR</i> ]

29:03.249 --> 29:07.584
<i>Let me out!</i>

29:08.987 --> 29:12.055
<i>This is not right!</i>

29:12.090 --> 29:13.923
[ <i> SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY</i> ]

29:16.094 --> 29:17.560
I looked into Kool & Klean.

29:17.595 --> 29:19.562
Their product is highly suspect,

29:19.597 --> 29:23.399
their support nonexistent,
but nothing illegal.

29:23.434 --> 29:25.669
- Nothing?
- Sorry.

29:28.542 --> 29:30.707
That's... shameful.

29:30.742 --> 29:33.609
I know. The company's a mess,
but the law is very clear on...

29:33.645 --> 29:35.044
I'm not talking about Kool & Klean.

29:35.079 --> 29:36.612
I'm talking about you.
All of you. This office.

29:36.648 --> 29:37.742
I'm sorry?

29:37.778 --> 29:39.948
This company is stealing people's money.

29:39.984 --> 29:42.084
Their life savings. And you have
nothing to say about it.

29:42.119 --> 29:43.118
Just, "Oh."

29:43.154 --> 29:46.322
Rodrigo Puente,
who hurt no one, does 10 years,

29:46.357 --> 29:48.390
and you can't do anything about this?

29:48.425 --> 29:51.927
Your dad made a bad deal.
It's frustrating. I get it.

29:51.962 --> 29:52.961
But I didn't write the law

29:52.997 --> 29:56.065
and I don't set the priorities
in this office.

29:58.669 --> 30:00.969
I thought you were different.

30:01.742 --> 30:04.739
A lot of people in your office
have this problem with me.

30:04.774 --> 30:10.078
♪♪

30:10.113 --> 30:16.451
♪♪

30:16.486 --> 30:19.187
I've been waiting for this
moment for a long time.

30:19.223 --> 30:22.123
And here is what I want to say to you...

30:22.638 --> 30:24.092
Where is the elevator?

30:24.127 --> 30:25.093
Right behind you.

30:25.128 --> 30:26.493
Thank you.

30:26.529 --> 30:29.097
♪♪

30:29.132 --> 30:30.631
I never took you for an animal...

30:30.666 --> 30:31.799
I'M NOT!

30:31.835 --> 30:33.901
Okay, well...

30:36.139 --> 30:38.606
Mr. Gunn, you may proceed.

30:48.050 --> 30:51.151
Ten seconds.
That was 10 seconds. Only 10.

30:51.186 --> 30:52.720
But enough for you to wonder,

30:52.755 --> 30:54.520
"What's happening? What's wrong?"

30:54.556 --> 30:56.556
Enough time to make you feel
uncomfortable.

30:56.591 --> 30:58.391
Unnerved.

30:58.426 --> 31:00.894
Impatient. Anxious.

31:00.929 --> 31:03.130
In the four days after Kirk Keener

31:03.165 --> 31:05.331
locked Brian Torres in Holding Room 3,

31:05.367 --> 31:11.036
Brian experienced that 34,560 times.

31:11.072 --> 31:12.472
In a row.

31:12.507 --> 31:14.206
And each time it got worse.

31:14.242 --> 31:16.743
Time flies when you're having fun.

31:16.778 --> 31:19.211
It stops when you're being tortured.

31:19.247 --> 31:20.880
And this was torture.

31:21.697 --> 31:25.851
Four days in an unheated, airless tomb.

31:25.887 --> 31:28.654
No food. No water. No bathroom.

31:28.689 --> 31:32.524
No windows. No voices.

31:33.875 --> 31:35.227
No hope.

31:35.263 --> 31:38.461
Ms. Carlan will tell you this
happened because of a mistake.

31:38.497 --> 31:40.173
This was not a mistake.

31:40.935 --> 31:43.502
Because you do not make
mistakes like this.

31:44.238 --> 31:46.705
Mr. Keener certainly doesn't.
He's a professional.

31:46.740 --> 31:50.241
He knows what he's doing.
And he knew what he was doing.

31:50.277 --> 31:54.045
"Leave... that son
of a bitch... in there."

31:54.080 --> 31:55.246
That's what he said.

31:55.282 --> 31:57.949
This was arrogance. This was contempt.

31:57.984 --> 32:02.086
This was a man and a system

32:02.122 --> 32:05.991
that believes the little people can be...

32:07.993 --> 32:11.229
swept up, loaded up, locked away.

32:11.264 --> 32:14.708
Forgotten. This was cruelty.
This was torture.

32:17.169 --> 32:19.303
This was not a mistake.

32:19.339 --> 32:22.239
The mistake will be in not
holding Mr. Keener accountable.

32:22.274 --> 32:24.241
The mistake will be in letting those

32:24.276 --> 32:28.555
charged with enforcing the law,
stand above it.

32:29.281 --> 32:32.559
The mistake will be in allowing
Brian Torres to be left alone.

32:33.752 --> 32:35.418
Again.

32:36.655 --> 32:40.891
Brian Torres is by every account
a good and decent man.

32:40.926 --> 32:43.260
An innocent man. A victim.

32:43.295 --> 32:46.263
We do not dispute this.
We acknowledge this.

32:46.298 --> 32:47.998
We respect this.

32:48.033 --> 32:51.000
But, while we all here grieve
for Brian Torres,

32:51.035 --> 32:53.970
that is not why we are here.

32:54.005 --> 32:57.741
That is not why you are here.

32:57.776 --> 33:01.344
You are here to determine if Kirk Keener

33:01.380 --> 33:06.115
did willfully deprive
Mr. Torres of his rights.

33:06.150 --> 33:08.317
Willfully. Willfully.

33:08.353 --> 33:10.819
Did he intend to do this?

33:10.855 --> 33:16.125
And the answer to that question
is simply... no.

33:16.160 --> 33:19.762
Mr. Gunn is a strong
and formidable attorney,

33:19.797 --> 33:24.366
and knowing that he had no case
here, he tried to make a case.

33:24.402 --> 33:28.804
Out of that video.
Out of emotion and fear.

33:28.839 --> 33:32.207
And there is reason to be
fearful here. There is.

33:32.242 --> 33:33.776
But the fear should not be

33:33.811 --> 33:36.645
that what happened to
Brian Torres will happen to you.

33:36.680 --> 33:38.714
Because what happened to Brian Torres,

33:38.749 --> 33:42.317
while excruciating, is mercifully rare.

33:42.352 --> 33:44.719
The fear is, and should be,

33:44.754 --> 33:48.356
that what is happening to Kirk Keener

33:48.392 --> 33:50.158
could happen to you.

33:50.193 --> 33:53.728
That because of a mistake,
because of an accident,

33:53.763 --> 33:57.799
because of one moment
of real human frailty,

33:57.834 --> 34:00.668
the full weight of
the United States government

34:00.703 --> 34:04.038
will bear down upon you
and you will be swept up,

34:04.073 --> 34:06.741
loaded up, locked away.

34:06.776 --> 34:09.009
Put in a box.

34:09.739 --> 34:12.512
Forgotten.

34:12.547 --> 34:14.415
And no one will feel bad for you

34:14.449 --> 34:18.252
because you will just be... a criminal.

34:22.833 --> 34:24.568
How can Seth say there's no case?

34:24.603 --> 34:26.636
Scamming hardworking people
isn't wrongdoing anymore?

34:26.672 --> 34:28.004
I think he doesn't want the case

34:28.040 --> 34:29.505
because prosecutors only want cases

34:29.542 --> 34:31.042
that are big and splashy

34:31.077 --> 34:32.242
and can make their careers for them.

34:32.277 --> 34:34.143
You know how they are, right?
Oh, I know how they are.

34:34.179 --> 34:36.413
So, fine, I'll make this one
big and splashy.

34:36.449 --> 34:38.313
I'll go to the... Stop.

34:39.411 --> 34:40.350
Sit down.

34:40.375 --> 34:41.340
What?

34:41.478 --> 34:42.744
Sit.

34:50.445 --> 34:52.078
For real. Okay?

34:52.574 --> 34:53.813
Okay.

34:53.848 --> 34:56.315
From what I can tell,
your dad made a mistake.

34:56.350 --> 34:58.350
He wasn't seduced, he wasn't tricked.

34:58.386 --> 35:00.219
He did something dumb. And human.

35:00.254 --> 35:01.587
My dad isn't dumb.

35:01.623 --> 35:03.523
My dad was an electrical
engineer in Syria.

35:03.558 --> 35:04.624
He has two graduate degrees.

35:04.659 --> 35:07.059
And when he couldn't get a job
here as an engineer,

35:07.094 --> 35:08.861
he built a small business out of nothing.

35:08.897 --> 35:10.523
He's maybe the smartest person I know,

35:10.559 --> 35:12.231
and I know some very smart people.

35:12.266 --> 35:14.566
Then maybe listen to what
they're telling you.

35:15.937 --> 35:20.372
My mom, later on in her life,
needed help with various things.

35:20.408 --> 35:22.574
Personal things. Hygiene things.

35:22.609 --> 35:24.376
When I'd have to help her in that way,

35:24.412 --> 35:25.911
she'd do this strange thing,

35:25.947 --> 35:29.948
she'd just laugh and say,
"Flippity-flop!"

35:30.403 --> 35:31.750
I didn't know what it was,

35:31.785 --> 35:36.955
I thought it was a silly noise
to make, out of embarrassment.

35:37.285 --> 35:40.792
But I finally asked her
what in the hell that meant.

35:41.581 --> 35:45.964
And she said, "It means...

35:46.503 --> 35:49.934
now I'm the baby, and you're the mom."

35:51.972 --> 35:53.104
My parents aren't old.

35:53.139 --> 35:54.386
I know.

35:55.428 --> 35:58.909
But at some point, it's how it goes.

35:58.945 --> 36:01.979
Sons become fathers, fathers become sons.

36:02.014 --> 36:04.915
Heroes become flesh and blood.

36:04.951 --> 36:07.284
♪♪

36:07.319 --> 36:09.653
Flippity-flop.

36:09.689 --> 36:15.459
♪♪

36:15.495 --> 36:18.761
In the case of United States
versus Kirk Keener,

36:18.797 --> 36:21.830
we the jury find the defendant,
Kirk Keener...

36:22.834 --> 36:25.935
not guilty of one count
of deprivation of civil rights

36:25.971 --> 36:27.270
under color of law.

36:27.306 --> 36:31.774
♪♪

36:31.810 --> 36:33.009
Thank you.

36:33.044 --> 36:34.010
Mm-hmm.

36:34.045 --> 36:39.849
♪♪

36:39.885 --> 36:45.655
♪♪

36:45.690 --> 36:52.328
♪♪

36:58.403 --> 37:01.270
Well, you finally beat me.

37:01.305 --> 37:03.506
I kind of beat you last time,

37:03.541 --> 37:06.842
but, anyway, it wasn't me.

37:06.877 --> 37:08.010
No, it wasn't.

37:08.045 --> 37:09.978
But your side did win.

37:10.014 --> 37:12.047
Or my side did. I'm not sure anymore.

37:12.082 --> 37:15.651
Anyway, congratulations.

37:15.686 --> 37:17.619
Thank you.

37:20.057 --> 37:22.657
I realize I've never seen
your happy face before,

37:22.692 --> 37:24.125
but if this is it?

37:24.161 --> 37:25.560
It needs work.

37:25.595 --> 37:30.331
♪♪

37:30.367 --> 37:32.467
We will not <i> allow</i> these smugglers

37:32.502 --> 37:33.901
to shamelessly exploit...

37:33.937 --> 37:35.870
<i>We</i> will not allow these smugglers

37:35.905 --> 37:37.372
to shamelessly exploit...

37:37.407 --> 37:39.339
Homemade baklava. From Jay Simmons.

37:39.375 --> 37:41.909
Well, probably his mom,
but still Jay-adjacent.

37:41.945 --> 37:43.510
His version of an apology.

37:43.546 --> 37:45.079
And since he was your antagonist,

37:45.114 --> 37:46.847
I thought you might want...

37:46.883 --> 37:49.650
I mean, I walk into this office,

37:49.686 --> 37:52.920
and it's like being
on the Jungle Cruise now.

37:52.956 --> 37:54.889
You've gone full animal.

37:54.924 --> 37:58.024
Is there anybody more into
animals than you at this point?

37:58.060 --> 38:00.394
You're off the hook on this
wildlife case, Littlejohn.

38:00.429 --> 38:02.662
What? What are you talking about?

38:02.698 --> 38:04.264
Smuggler's attorney went behind our backs

38:04.300 --> 38:05.332
to the State Department.

38:05.367 --> 38:07.267
Her guy offered up a bigger guy.
It's been settled.

38:07.303 --> 38:08.835
Please tell me they got warheads

38:08.870 --> 38:10.036
or political prisoners out of this.

38:10.072 --> 38:13.974
Black-market Chinese tobacco.
Apparently that's... something.

38:17.980 --> 38:19.178
I'm sorry.

38:19.214 --> 38:21.180
Oh, no. God. Nothing to be sorry about.

38:21.216 --> 38:24.350
I tried to defend these f-furry things,

38:24.385 --> 38:25.885
and now I don't have to.

38:25.921 --> 38:28.021
I'm happy. This is good.

38:28.056 --> 38:33.559
♪♪

38:33.595 --> 38:40.133
♪♪

38:40.168 --> 38:42.368
♪ I know you ♪

38:42.403 --> 38:43.685
Hi.

38:43.721 --> 38:45.738
- ♪ You're worrying all the time ♪
- What are you...?

38:45.773 --> 38:47.973
I had a meeting upstairs.
I thought I'd stop by.

38:48.009 --> 38:51.744
Well, this is it. What do you think?

38:51.779 --> 38:52.911
It's nice.

38:52.947 --> 38:54.713
Overhead lighting's a little harsh.

38:54.749 --> 38:56.548
And you could use an outdoor window.

38:56.583 --> 38:58.250
Really tall doors.

38:58.285 --> 38:59.618
Okay. I get it.

38:59.654 --> 39:01.120
You sure? 'Cause I got more.

39:01.155 --> 39:03.087
Yeah. I'm good.

39:03.123 --> 39:04.194
♪ Don't know what I'd do ♪

39:04.230 --> 39:06.958
Well, in that case, I'm gonna head home.

39:06.993 --> 39:10.395
I was just about to break
into this baklava from Jay,

39:10.430 --> 39:11.996
if you want to hang out for a minute.

39:12.032 --> 39:17.569
♪ I wish you didn't take on
everybody's pain ♪

39:17.604 --> 39:20.138
♪ 'Cause I know you ♪

39:20.173 --> 39:21.906
I get the smaller piece?

39:21.941 --> 39:23.107
You're not my girlfriend anymore.

39:23.143 --> 39:24.942
Small price to pay.

39:24.978 --> 39:27.679
♪ Don't know what I'd do if I
lost you ♪ - How's your mom?

39:27.714 --> 39:30.114
Any big scores at the
"Antiques Roadshow" lately?

39:30.150 --> 39:33.785
$5,000 on a comb
that belonged to Gerald Ford.

39:33.820 --> 39:34.652
No way!

39:34.687 --> 39:36.520
Got the certificate and everything.

39:36.556 --> 39:38.109
[CHUCKLES]

39:39.358 --> 39:42.159
♪ So don't go ♪

39:42.195 --> 39:46.830
♪ Don't go on me now ♪

39:46.865 --> 39:49.099
♪ Don't go ♪

39:49.134 --> 39:53.003
You know, I can help.
I'm making good money now.

39:53.038 --> 39:54.871
♪♪

39:54.907 --> 39:58.175
I can help... pay off that thing.

39:58.210 --> 40:02.012
Help? You live with your parents.

40:02.047 --> 40:04.047
Who can you help?

40:04.083 --> 40:05.982
Forget it.

40:06.018 --> 40:07.883
♪♪

40:07.919 --> 40:09.519
I'm the father.

40:09.554 --> 40:11.654
This is my family.

40:11.690 --> 40:13.789
I take care of the family.

40:13.825 --> 40:16.859
♪ I swear I'm coming, too ♪

40:16.894 --> 40:19.028
♪ 'Cause I don't know what I'd do ♪

40:19.063 --> 40:20.996
This is how he got his name.

40:21.032 --> 40:24.200
He eats a lot of greens,
but he loves mango.

40:24.235 --> 40:25.467
Do you want to feed him?

40:25.502 --> 40:28.971
♪ Don't know what I'd do if I
lost you ♪ - Uh, yes, I would.

40:29.006 --> 40:30.672
Here.

40:31.736 --> 40:32.854
Hi.

40:32.889 --> 40:34.309
♪ So don't go ♪

40:34.345 --> 40:35.711
Hey, Mango.

40:35.747 --> 40:38.080
♪ Don't go ♪

40:38.116 --> 40:39.314
I'm Kate.

40:39.350 --> 40:43.151
♪ Don't go ♪

40:43.186 --> 40:47.188
♪ Don't grow old on me now ♪

40:47.224 --> 40:49.190
I know the last time we met,

40:49.226 --> 40:51.560
uh, you wanted to talk
about Judge Cameron.

40:51.595 --> 40:52.728
I have an update for you.

40:52.763 --> 40:53.729
You okay?

40:53.764 --> 40:55.163
- I'm fine.
- You look like hell.

40:55.198 --> 40:57.065
You should see me when I'm not fine.

40:57.100 --> 40:58.332
Have you slept?

40:58.368 --> 40:59.901
Not recently.

40:59.936 --> 41:03.738
♪♪

41:03.774 --> 41:05.373
I don't know how you do it.

41:05.408 --> 41:07.408
Losing all the time.

41:07.443 --> 41:09.778
I find a way to find a win.

41:09.813 --> 41:13.881
Even if it's just the look
in your eyes. Knowing I tried.

41:13.916 --> 41:16.284
I don't sleep much.

41:16.319 --> 41:18.218
♪ Don't go ♪

41:18.254 --> 41:21.054
- You did the right thing.
- I know.

41:21.090 --> 41:22.390
♪ Don't go ♪

41:22.425 --> 41:24.091
I'm sorry.

41:24.126 --> 41:26.193
For what I said.

41:27.330 --> 41:28.763
Can we get out of here?

41:28.798 --> 41:31.631
- [SCOFFS]
